<subSubSection id="B2D6B2DC4109E90D6BCDD719FBB62007" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="FA73E1574109E90D6BCDD719FAF72393" blockId="33.[151,1436,369,609]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
<emphasis id="C8B83D454109E90D6BCDD719FEDD23EC" bold="true" box="[151,266,369,394]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Ventral edge of ovipositor sheath straight or slightly curved downwards in species with long ovipositor, tip knife-shaped with dorsal edge sloping down and ventral edge almost straight (
<figureCitation id="62F7FDD24109E90D6F7ED7FDFB1623CB" box="[1060,1217,405,429]" captionStart="FIGURES 105–120" captionStartId="74.[151,263,1801,1824]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1780]" captionTargetId="figure-34@74.[151,1436,193,1780]" captionTargetPageId="74" captionText="FIGURES 105–120. Ovipositor sheaths of Xyela species. All figures at same scale. Legend: HT—holotype; NT—neotype; PT—paratype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5261380" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5261380/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Figs 105–117</figureCitation>
), sensilla field with 3–4 setae (
<figureCitation id="62F7FDD24109E90D6A55D7D1FEB423B7" box="[271,355,441,465]" captionStart="FIGURES 86–94" captionStartId="72.[151,263,1935,1958]" captionTargetBox="[151,1414,177,1915]" captionTargetId="figure-71@72.[151,1415,177,1915]" captionTargetPageId="72" captionText="FIGURES 86–94. Ovipositor sheath, sensilla pattern and sensilla plate (spl) at the apex of the ovipositor sheath. 86, Xyela helvetica. 87, X. longula, arrows indicate the modified hairs at apex of valvula 1. 88, X. lugdunensis. 89, X. meridionalis. 90–91, X. alpigena. 92–93, X. curva. 94, X. densiflorae." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5261376" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5261376/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Fig. 94</figureCitation>
); valvula 1 distally with 12–14 oblique, closely spaced annuli (similar to 
<figureCitation id="62F7FDD24109E90D6FCCD7D1FB3F23B7" box="[1174,1256,441,465]" captionStart="FIGURES 86–94" captionStartId="72.[151,263,1935,1958]" captionTargetBox="[151,1414,177,1915]" captionTargetId="figure-71@72.[151,1415,177,1915]" captionTargetPageId="72" captionText="FIGURES 86–94. Ovipositor sheath, sensilla pattern and sensilla plate (spl) at the apex of the ovipositor sheath. 86, Xyela helvetica. 87, X. longula, arrows indicate the modified hairs at apex of valvula 1. 88, X. lugdunensis. 89, X. meridionalis. 90–91, X. alpigena. 92–93, X. curva. 94, X. densiflorae." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5261376" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5261376/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Fig. 94</figureCitation>
); lateral lamella of valviceps oblique, medial lobe strikingly protruding above proximal and distal lobes (
<figureCitation id="62F7FDD24109E90D6F2ED7B5FAC42393" box="[1140,1299,477,501]" captionStart-0="FIGURES 136–145" captionStart-1="FIGURES 146–156" captionStartId-0="77.[151,263,1745,1768]" captionStartId-1="78.[151,263,1865,1888]" captionTargetBox-0="[151,1436,193,1706]" captionTargetBox-1="[151,1436,193,1843]" captionTargetId-0="figure-41@77.[151,1436,193,1725]" captionTargetId-1="figure-75@78.[151,1436,193,1844]" captionTargetPageId-0="77" captionTargetPageId-1="78" captionText-0="FIGURES 136–145. Penis valves of Xyela species: X. curva group, X. julii group (part). Figs 138–139 and 141 reproduced from Blank et al. (2005)." captionText-1="FIGURES 146–156. Penis valves of Xyela species (X. julii group, part), and male external copulatory apparatus of Xyela in ventral and lateral view. 153–154, X. longula (penis valves removed). 155–156, X. curva (penis valves and volsellae removed). Legend: bpa—basiparamere, br—basal ring, gon—gonomacula, har—harpe, lap—lateral apodeme, vol—volsella. Figs 147, 150 and 152 reproduced from Blank et al. (2005)." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5261388" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5261390" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/5261388/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/5261390/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Figs 141–152</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FA73E1574109E90D6B9DD469FBB62007" blockId="33.[151,1436,369,609]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
